ed aspects of postcolonial societies, and provocative remarks on humanism and cosmopolitanism, Flesh and Fish Blood opens up new horizons of theoretical possibility for postcolonial studies and cultural analysis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aIndic literaturexTranslationsxHistory and criticism. 0aIndic literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPostcolonialism in motion pictures. 0aPostmodernism (Literature)zIndia. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / General.2bisacsh  aasian culture.  aasian literacy criticism.  abook club books.  abooks about cultural analysis.  abooks about different cultures.  abooks about literature and film.  abooks for history lovers.  acosmopolitanism.  acultural spaces.  aculture lovers.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aenglish.  afeminism.  ahindi.  ahistorical.  ahumanism.  aindian literature.  aleisure reads.  apostcolonial studies.  apostmodernism literacy criticism.  arealistic.  asouth asian culture.  atamil dalit.  atamil.  avacation reads.  avernacular analysis.  avernacular studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027252140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095234840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520952348423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520952348/original  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY